* That pissed her right off when Prowl hissed back at her.
The nerve!
It was good to feel the ground under her feet again before Prowl had hissed 
and started to fly off towards Astroblast.  Shaking herself she growled and 
glared at him as he just began to fly away, snarling and snapping at the tip 
of his tail, meaning clear that she didn't like his attetude. Which she 
didn't.
This was getting out of hand!
Prowl was in the same mode as her except with feathers and wings and his 
logic was gone. It just didn't seem right.  Even she wasn't this bad when 
she was first created, or she at least didn't remember being that bad.
Must be a male thing.
< Thinks he can get away with anything!> was her thoughts.
She just hoped that the nip got through to him and he'de learn to keep his 
manners around her.*
